r s BC-BKN-MAVERICKS-TEX     10-09 0175
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-MAVERICKS-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PACK'S INJURY NOT TROUBLING NELSON
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By DWAIN PRICE 
c.1999 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   DALLAS _ Mavericks point guard Robert Pack strained his right
hamstring in last night's scrimmage, but Mavericks trainer Roger
Hinds and coach/general manager Don Nelson said the injury was
``nothing serious.''
</P>
<P>
   The injury sent Pack to the sidelines, where he received some
ice treatment. The eight-year veteran had subsequent treatments in
the locker room near the end of practice while teammates finished
free-throw drills.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's more fatigue than anything else,'' Hinds said. ``They've
been going at it pretty hard lately.''
</P>
<P>
   Pack has missed portions of the past six seasons with various
injuries. He was sidelined for half of last season's
strike-shortened 50 games with a torn right hamstring and surgery
to repair a dislocated left shoulder.
</P>
<P>
   Point guard Steve Nash also left the evening practice early for
the second consecutive day with recurring pain in his right ankle.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
