<P>
   WIS-WELFARE _ Wisconsin, of all places, suddenly has the jitters
about cutting families off welfare. Since 1996, the state's
famously tough work rules have swept more than 57,000 families from
the rolls and turned a war on welfare into a social experiment
commanding international attention. But Wisconsin is now grappling
with the ultimate symbol of the new welfare age: time limits. By
Jason DeParle.
</P>
