   FOLD
</P>
<P>
   KANSAS-CREATIONISM _ Scientific lessons about the origins of
life have long been challenged in public schools, but some Bible
literalists are now adding the reigning theory about the origin of
the universe to their list of targets. Nearly overlooked in the
furor over the Kansas Board of Education's decision in August to
remove evolution from its education standards was a decision to
delete from its standards a description of the Big Bang theory of
cosmic origins. By James Glanz.
</P>
<P>
   (We plan to move the story by noon ET in ``a'' news file.)
</P>
<P>
   REPUBS-BUSH-DELAY (Washington) _ There are a couple of leading
theories about the relationship between the two Texas Republicans
who may soon be running the country: A) That the party's
presidential front-runner, Gov. George W. Bush, and House Majority
Whip Tom DeLay are closer than we know. B) That these two guys from
opposite sides of the tracks have little to nothing in common. By
