<P>
   GREECE-OLYMPICS _ ATHENS, Greece _ The city that gave birth to
the Modern Games in 1896 now faces the challenge of staging the
21st Century version of the revived Greek competitions. With all
the problems of logistics, politics and economics _ problems which
did more to help Atlanta win the 1996 Games than any wining and
dining _ will the Games die in their cradle? Or, will the 2004
Games showcase Athens as the modern European city it wants to be?
(Roughton, Cox News Service). WITH PHOTOS. MOVED FRIDAY to the (i)
International and (s) Sports categories.
</P>
<P>
   CHECHNYA-REFUGEES _ NAZRAN, Russia _ The destitute refugees
fleeing Russian bombs and bullets have seen it all before. But this
sequel to the war in Chechnya could have been avoided, they say, if
only both sides would talk. But the innocent refugees streaming out
of Chechnya say they are trapped between Moscow's imperial attitude
toward the southern republic and ruthless Chechen warlords who will
stop at nothing short of an independent Islamic state. They see no
exit from war, for themselves or Russia. This reprise of the War in
Chechnya, they say, will be as bloody and senseless as the first
one that raged from 1994-96. (Holmes, Cox News Service). WITH
PHOTOS. MOVED FRIDAY.
</P>
