CRIME-RING _ Potential witnesses against an Arizona crime syndicate
have been shot down, derailing years of undercover work and
squelching an indictment against the suspected ringleaders. At
least four men are dead, including a key witness. The homicide
victims all were associates of Luis A. and Felipe ``Porky''
Cisneros, both of whom have served prison time. Three of the
killings were committed before the Cisneros brothers were to stand
trial last year on 14 felony charges, including possession of
stolen property and operating a chop shop. By DENNIS WAGNER. Story
will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
