Arizona threatens the state's natural wildlife and costs the state
millions of dollars a year. Two prime offenders in the state are
the tamarisk, or salt cedar, and red brome grass, according to
officials. By JOHN STANLEY. Story will move in the ``A'' category. &QL; 
 &QL; 
MONTINI-COLUMN _ (Phoenix) To news junkies, the most dangerously
addictive narcotic is something we call the ``exclusive.'' If you
want to get a reporter hooked, slip him an ``exclusive'' and he'll
completely lose touch with reality. I've seen it happen lots of of
times, maybe because the most successful ``exclusive'' dealer in
the country operates right here in Arizona. His name is U.S. Sen.
John McCain. By E.J. MONTINI. Story will move in the ``A'' and
``K'' categories. &QL; 
 &QL; 
